      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Be careful.  There are many more developmental anti-patterns that rely on <code>ordinal()</code> than valid use cases for <code>ordinal()</code>.  If you need to store a unique value for the <code>enum</code>, then just store the <code>enum</code>.  There are EnumSets, Lists of Enums, EnumMaps, and nearly any other Enum collection you might want available."
