      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@DarrelHoffman My feeling is that doing that is fine, since the only strong arguments I see against using <code>ordinal()</code> hinge on far flung code being broken by changes to the enum enumeration constants. If you&#39;re going to modify the enum&#39;s constants you&#39;d have to be in that file already. Most enums are fairly short, and if it&#39;s not you should be checking the file more thoroughly anyway. In both cases you should probably have a unit test covering your <code>next()</code> method anyway."
    } ],
