      "creation_date" : 1680102809,
      "post_id" : 15940036,
      "comment_id" : 133841244,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "I think it really depends what you&#39;re using the ordinal value for.  Serialization would be dangerous, but as display order for a sort or something similar it could be harmless and changing the sort order by reordering items in code is less risky on a large list than updating dozens of magic numbers to non-sequential values."
    } ],
