      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Doesn&#39;t this have the disadvantage of trying to pass an enum value to a method? You can no longer pass a XLINK to a method, because it doesn&#39;t represent anything concrete. You lose the typing into your method. The method signature would have to read short instead of XLINK."
